"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"*Originally published September 15th, 2015*\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/aqUM2HAhag3iMn2QhYCbJ.png?height=771&width=1542&size=medium)\\n\\nI had the privilege of being a guest lecturer at UCLA earlier this year to their Economics 106E: Startups class. It’s incredibly rewarding to be able to give back to my alma mater and help inspire/educate the next generation of entrepreneurs.\\n\\nEvery time I give a presentation like this, I am careful to balance the “goods and the bads” of living the startup life.. It’s a major red flag to me when people want to join startups because they’re, “cool”- it feels like a professional obligation to share the ups and downs of the journey.\\n\\nI hope you enjoy watching this presentation as much as I enjoyed delivering it:\\n\\n[https://youtu.be/JnrpXGUWvs4](https://youtu.be/JnrpXGUWvs4)\\n\\n[https://www.slideshare.net/JohnMilinovich/good-idea-bad-startup-ucla-econ-106e](https://www.slideshare.net/JohnMilinovich/good-idea-bad-startup-ucla-econ-106e)\\n\\n\",\"timestamp\":1640308461,\"title\":\"Good Idea, Bad Startup\"},\"digest\":\"k2pZw1Y_C2yqUFpd132hwhsDdf94g4qoqTmNRCpl6mg\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xCfdC2419f4CC439A064d9A5334cbEF203b135921\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"I8En9f6cctrn5MYA4nb-kdKWBAZaNuz8xOrmHd1dNNA\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"3y_lCfYvKfnEstqKamKIjtFdX9up-I5APpNaSDJrdlA\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"QtqlHV0vmg9fo4RMXhr6Rbk3E-_oNKb1QwLUulxjpP21XV9wpJLAvFsTh0n0w4JIaE9F7lbBs4pjvdXQ85fFPA\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x67a7102172a35297a9e10f750a59322485845e0713ab7ecaac0660e059d097ef73095a7a844dcb8edf8dca054aeb54655a3a599157b5847da0d1918ff83853621c\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"I8En9f6cctrn5MYA4nb-kdKWBAZ